				<center>	<i id="qoute">	"I've learned that people will forget what you said,<br> people will forget what you did,<br> but people will never forget how you made them feel."</i><br> -Maya Angelou</center>
					</p>
					
					
					<h3>Empulada</h3>
					<p>Lorna Dee Cervantes portrays her struggle in one of the poems with an excessively long title called “POEM FOR THE YOUNG WHITE MAN WHO ASKED ME HOW I, AN INTELLIGENT, WELLREAD PERSON COULD BELIEVE IN THE WAR BETWEEN RACES”. She portrays her struggle because there is a lot of racism in the world. She writes about the struggles she goes through in everyday life and how her own culture is disrespected by white America. Lorna was born in San Francisco in 1954 and I believe there was a lot of racism against her culture when she was growing up. There is still racism going on in America and the current president now is a threat to our society because we live in such a diverse community. America is supposed to be the land of the free but now we are headed in the wrong direction. We are supposed to be a loving and thriving country and now we are building a wall to keep the people that helped this country grow, isn’t it ironic? The war between the races needs to end and we should all be treated equally. I am half Chilean as well and have dealt with racism growing up.</p>
