					<h3>M. Butterfly</h3>
					<p>In the true story, Madame Butterfly. The protagonist of the film, Rene Gallimard is mentally blind because he has been stuck in his fantasy of the play. He has been going to this play so much and begins to fall in love with the Chinese opera star Song Liling. Rene sees Song as the perfect women and starts interacting with her. They fall in love and Rene becomes mentally blind because he is so in love with her. Rene doesn’t understand that Song is a man during the whole story. This is wild because Song would have to be on point all the time, in the movie Songs voice does not sound feminine and would immediately throw me off.</p>
